metadata.name: HexaCity #127
metadata.description:
The idea of designing an urban facade came to my mind in 2019, but it was postponed for various reasons. A few months ago I refocused on this project and after reviewing the available examples I decided to use a specific style to implement it.
This algorithm depicts an isometric view of a city. Therefore, the basis of this algorithm is isometric design.
Isometric drawing comes from the Greek "iso metro," meaning equal measure. This is because the angle between the x, y, and z axes is 120°. It's a form of axonometric perspective (there is no foreshortening). In other words, face lines are all drawn from the same angle.
The advantage of drawing this way is that an object can be freely rotated, re-positioned, and reoriented without redrawing it. There is also no change in scale when an object is moved forward or backward.
One of the features of using this style is that with a suitable combination of colors at different angles, you can quickly achieve 3D output with a 2D design.
Each building is individually designed after determining its height with a random algorithm, then one of dozens of random roof design algorithms is called for finalization.
Two types of scale combinations have been used for building scale, one is buildings with the same scale. In this combination, large-scale structures are formed when buildings are placed next to each other. And in other compositions, the integration of different scales creates more depth and variety.
Made by p5.js
s = save

metadata.name: Bound #30
metadata.description:
Our journey consists of events that happen one after the other, and most of the time these are quite linear. The parts we remember and cherish often happen when we change paths. "Bound" is about letting go and being open to events that are unpredictable and thus gaining new colorfull experiences. 

This collection exists of connected rectangles on a tight grid with lines cutting their way through the patterns made with a simple algorithm.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje November 2022

metadata.name: Return to Apophenia #15
metadata.description:
Fxhash turns one!
Revenue from initial sales divided 50% 40% 10% between Savepakistan, Processing Foundation and the artist.

Apophenia was my first project on fxhash. It seemed fitting to return to this concept for my anniversary mint and recreate it anew, employing many of the skills I have learned over the last year.

It has some fun interaction...

Mouse click in the centre of a hexagon to rotate that hexagon.
Hexagons have 1,2,3 or 6 unique rotations.

On the keyboard:
'c' to regenerate the work with the colours of the palette rotated
'r' to recreate the work with re-randomised hexagons
't' to change the edge tiles so that the complete image becomes a seamlessly tiling rectangle
'y' to generate a symmetrical image with the same scale and colour palette - this will use different hexagons from the original image and any further interaction will act on the original image, not the symmetrical pattern, which almost certainly won't tile

keys 2 through 9 to render at increasing resolutions

's' to save a .png of the current canvas

26 palettes with random rotations + 12 unique hexagons + 10 hexagon combinations + lots of scale and layout possibilities = virtual infinity

Created with p5.js

metadata.name: pantonX.3 #126
metadata.description:
pantonX.3
is the third drop of the zukuNFT project, which is dedicated to geometric and minimalist standards of early geometric art.
inspired by the "bauhaus grundkurs" based on the didactic concepts of the bauhaus (1919-1933) and its teachings by johannes itten, paul klee, wassily kandinsky, lászló moholy-nagy and josef albers. the preliminary courses and their basic design tasks dealt syntactically with circle, line and square as well as color, and contrasts.

i am a visual artist and have worked in the field of coding since the early years of processing.
always loved geometric and minimalist art, bauhaus, de stijl, piet mondrian, sol leWitt -- just to name a few -- and last but not least verner panton, have had a influence on my artistic work.

library: p5js
"s" key for saving

bauhaus small writing

www.e-art.co

metadata.name: a pale reflection #125
metadata.description:
a canvas is prepared; grids and vignette applied.

marks are added (or not)

a drawing method is chosen

the drawing method is iterated, resulting in a heavily stippled image

the image is sent to a shader

various maths occur inside the shader

the resulting shaded image is then given a border

and thus to the screen

a pale reflection - original music here: https://rtsixty.bandcamp.com/track/pale-reflection 
listen while waiting to be signed.

99.9% of royalties to original minter.

metadata.name: Digital Lava Lamp #186
metadata.description:
All primary sales are donated to @threejs
Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60FPS rendering

In celebration of the anniversary of fxhash, here is a playful interactive simulation, that attempts to replicate the feeling of an abstract lava lamp in a digital world.

[ Controls ]
Play with the physics by dragging your cursor/finger...
Or let the simulation do its thing by staying outside of the frame

[ f ] - fullscreen
[ s ] - save an image
[ r ] - restart the simulation

Created with Three.js + rapier.js
Copyright (c) November 2022 Shaderism

metadata.name: Azulejo #137
metadata.description:
Azulejo is a generative work made with p5.js

Behind this artwork, the author (eduxdux) had made a lot of research about tiling, the main references for this work were Athos Bulcão, Alexandre Mancini, and "Azulejo da igrejinha" by Cândido Portinari.

This artwork has 8 color palettes and 7 tile styles.
If you have lucky you can have a fully filled tile.

This work is participating in the FxHash anniversary event (#fxhashturnsone) and 10% of the royalties go to the Save Pakistan

Eduxdux November 2022

metadata.name: Morixels Goose #217
metadata.description:
➡️ This is for the Morixels family and benefits those who own at least one of the Morixels tokens ⬅️

If you have a minimum of 1 NFTs from Morixels even Colabs or Mega Colab
We whitelist you for having a minimum of 1 Morixels Goose

You don't have Morixels?

Don't worry you can buy from the primary or the secondary market 👇

https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/morixels-mans


The Morixels Goose are unique Random Generated 1000 PFP NFTs.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 25 by 25 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution.
The number of Traits in this collection is 9 (168 layers) and it has the ability to make 42,674,688,000 NFTs.
Some ​layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Eikonal identities #160
metadata.description:
Works in the invisible
Inevitable shadows
Digital exorcism
Silicon catharsis


Eikonal
- Usually "eikonal equation" : the wave-like description of the propagation of light through a medium
- In optics, relative to the formation of an image
- anagram : e-kaolin



-----
* What/How *

Product of the code.

A picture generated by a succession of chaotic events applied to a system of 4.2 million particles.
The drawing process consists of mixing and projecting the particles randomly in space.

Each image is unique and depends only on the address of minter's wallet and current iteration number.

-----
* Technics *

- Hand written code in Javascript, GLSL
- Uses three.js library, WebGL particles, physics
- Generates a FullHD PNG (1080x1080 px bitmap 24bits)
- Takes less than 15 seconds of generation on a relatively recent GPU (>2017)

-----
@HAL09999 – August 8th, 2023
